<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-08-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-08-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="113" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d113">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Denby</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-08-27"><hi rend="italic">August 27,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Szechuan commission proceed as soon as British consul at Chungking can
                            leave his post, which is still impossible. Viceroy Liu is not to be
                            appointed commissioner, but has been ordered by imperial decree to stay
                            at his post until conduct investigated.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Denby</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>